{"lemma":"خَزَفُ","slug":"خَزَفُ","root":"خ.ز.ف","root_slug":"خ-ز-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ز-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10507"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"earthenware, ceramic, pottery"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Classical Syriac ܚܶܙܦܳܐ (ħezəpā), ܚܶܨܦܳܐ (ħeṣəpā, “piece of pottery”), related to ܚܰܙܽܘܦܳܐ (ḵazūpa, “rough”), which is a phono-semantic matching of Hittite 𒂁 (ḫarši-, “pottery vessel”). The Aramaic root is related to حَصَفَ (ḥaṣafa, “to twist a rope strongly”)."},"ipa":["/xa.zaf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10507","headword_ar":"خَزَفٌ","root":"xzf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pottery; jars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earthern vessels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, S, K; [and so in the present day;]) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything made of clay, and baked, so that it becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fax~aAr","text_ar":"فَخَّار"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IDrd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay made into vessels, before it is baked; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaloSaAlN","text_ar":"صَلْصَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": when baked, it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fax~aAr","text_ar":"فَخَّار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [See an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino","text_ar":"اـِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", p. 107.]"}],"source_refs":["IDrd","K"]}]}}